Description: Sherd of tall flaring foot of pottery krater with part of floor; buff clay; red-black glaze; floor and outside of foot glazed; graffito on inside of foot ring.
Curator's comments: Many aspects of the piece are unusual at Naukratis, noticably the size of the foot. The graffito is not readily interpreted in Greek
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.148)
